<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>Make sure you are part of the Administrator's group. Check with your system administrator to determine if you are in this group.</li>
            <li>In Windows, navigate to the Flare executable file (C:\Program Files\<MadCap:variable name="Other.CompanyName" />\MadCap Flare <MadCap:variable name="Other.VersionNumber" />\Flare.app\Flare.exe).</li>
            <li>Set yourself as an administrator for Flare (either temporarily or permanently).<p class="Subheading">to run only a single instance of flare as an administrator</p><ol class="LowerAlpha"><li>Right-click on the executable file.</li><li>Select <span class="Emphasis">Run as administrator</span>.</li></ol><p class="Subheading">to always run flare as an administrator</p><ol class="LowerAlpha"><li>Right-click on the executable file.</li><li>Select <span class="Emphasis">Properties</span>.</li><li>Select the <span class="Emphasis">Compatibility</span> tab.</li><li>In the <span class="Emphasis">Privilege Level</span> area, click in the check box labeled <span class="Emphasis">Run this program as an administrator</span>.</li></ol></li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>